   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Interpretation**\n",
    "\n",
    "The median node clustering is about **0.607**, while the median neighbor-average clustering is only about **0.021**. This gap shows that many characters belong to tiny closed local groups, but their neighbors are often connected to much broader and less closed parts of the network.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1a4ed3cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## **Week 5**\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d0784a0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Choice of Centrality Measures**\n",
    "\n",
    "We use two complementary notions of importance:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Betweenness centrality**, which rewards characters that sit on shortest paths and connect otherwise distant parts of the graph.\n",
    "- **PageRank**, which rewards characters connected to other important characters.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **5.1 Compute Betweenness and PageRank**\n",
    "\n",
    "We used the books definition, it defines betweenness of node `i` by counting the fraction of shortest paths between other nodes that pass through `i`:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "b_i=\\sum_{h\\ne j\\ne i}\\frac{\\sigma_{hj}(i)}{\\sigma_{hj}}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For PageRank, the book uses teleportation factor `alpha` and damping factor `1 - alpha`:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "R_t(i)=\\frac{\\alpha}{N}+(1-\\alpha)\\sum_{j\\in pred(i)}\\frac{R_{t-1}(j)}{k^{out}(j)}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: in `nx.pagerank`, the parameter `alpha` is the *damping* factor (= `1 - α_book`), so the call `nx.pagerank(G, alpha=0.85)` corresponds to teleportation 0.15 in the formula above.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "29fedaef",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-05-05T20:26:14.562136Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-05-05T20:26:14.562136Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-05-05T20:26:16.516749Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-05-05T20:26:16.513612Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "betweenness = nx.betweenness_centrality(G_week2, normalized=True)\n",
    "pagerank = nx.pagerank(G_week2, alpha=0.85)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7cb0bb9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Interpretation**\n",
    "\n",
    "The two measures capture different but related roles. Betweenness emphasizes bridging across episode groups and guest-character clusters, while PageRank emphasizes repeated connection to already central characters. Comparing them prevents the analysis from relying on a single definition of importance.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0614c0b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **5.2 Most Central Characters**\n",
    "\n",
    "We rank the top nodes under each score and measure how much the two top lists overlap. This overlap is an interpretation aid for the assignment, so it is described in prose rather than with an additional formula.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
