    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "subset = week10_summary[week10_summary[\"p\"] == 0.10]\n",
    "pivot_plot = subset.pivot(index=\"seed_size\", columns=\"origin\", values=\"avg_final_share\")\n",
    "ax = pivot_plot.plot(\n",
    "    kind=\"bar\",\n",
    "    figsize=(10, 6),\n",
    "    color=[\"#e76f51\", \"#2a9d8f\", \"#457b9d\"],\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"average final infected share\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Week 10 - ICM Scenario Comparison (p = 0.10)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0, pivot_plot.values.max() * 1.15)\n",
    "ax.legend(title=\"origin\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "47b72546",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Graph Analysis**\n",
    "\n",
    "At the same transmission probability, hub-origin cascades outperform random and peripheral cascades across seed sizes. The gap is especially visible for small outbreaks, where starting in the core gives the cascade immediate access to many parts of the network.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e4ed90d0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **10.4 Effect of Cascade Probability**\n",
    "\n",
    "We isolate hub-origin cascades and vary `p` to show how the transmission parameter changes final reach.\n"
   ]
  },
